	<div class="home_description">
	<p class="home_mission">Open Missouri is a project of the <%= link_to "Donald W. Reynolds Journalism Institute", "http://www.rjionline.org/ " %> at the <%= link_to "Missouri School of Journalism", "http://journalism.missouri.edu" %> in Columbia that aims to make state and local government information more available to journalists and citizens.</p>

	<p><strong>Open Missouri's goals are to:</strong>
		<ul>
			<li>Inform Missourians about public data held by government agencies.</li>

			<li>Inspire journalists, citizens, web developers, entrepreneurs, businesses and non-profits to access and use public data in ways that better their professional, civic and personal lives.</li>

			<li>Serve as a platform that connects people who are using data from state and local government agencies.</li>

			<li>Educate interested parties about how they can access and use public data.</li>
	</ul>
	</p>

	<p>RJI is funded by the <%= link_to "Donald W. Reynolds Foundation", "http://www.dwreynolds.org/" %>.</p>
